      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some minor, statistically insignificant variations in physiological traits can be observed across populations, these differences are incredibly subtle and do not translate into predictable athletic superiority for any specific race. The vast majority of athletic performance is driven by training, environment, and individual genetics, not broad racial groupings. Focusing on these minor, often disputed biological generalizations will likely distract from what actually drives fitness gains.",
