      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The arguments people make often rely on deeply flawed and outdated genetic determinism, which is scientifically unsound. Some older, highly controversial studies have attempted to link certain physical traits, like muscle fiber ratios, to ancestry, but these findings are not accepted as reliable predictors of performance. In modern sports science, these discussions are largely dismissed because the influence of environment and training overwhelmingly outweighs these minor, poorly defined supposed biological differences.",
      "source": "target",
